modules.description: This module provides functions to validate conditions and invariants in code, including equality checks, relational comparisons, exception handling, and timeouts. It operates on primitive types like booleans, integers, floats, and options, as well as arbitrary user-defined types. Concrete use cases include testing function outputs, enforcing preconditions, and debugging control flow.

This module converts OCaml values into their string representations, primarily for debugging or logging. It handles any OCaml type, including complex nested structures like lists, records, and variants. The `serialize` function outputs the full string representation, while `truncate` limits the output to approximately 100 characters for concise display.
